cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CE 

This paper deals with the problem of safety guarantees for learning-based controllers, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of control theory and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which is the primary category for papers on control theory. The paper also proposes a model predictive safety certification scheme, which involves optimization and decision-making, making it relevant to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses a practical data-based design procedure, which involves optimization and numerical methods, making it relevant to categories such as cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
